To install Node.js version 22 on Ubuntu, follow these steps:

Step 1: Update the package list
  sudo apt update

Step 2: Install prerequisites (Make sure you have the required dependencies installed for adding repositories).
  sudo apt install -y curl gnupg2 lsb-release ca-certificates


Step 3: Add NodeSource repository, To install Node.js version 22, you need to use the official NodeSource repository. Add NodeSource repository for Node.js 22.x: 
  curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_22.x | sudo -E  bash -

Install Node.js 22.x:
  sudo apt install -y nodejs

Step 4: Verify installation Once the installation is complete, check the installed version:
  node -v  


Install NPM :

Step 5: Install npm (if not installed) If npm (Node Package Manager) is not installed with Node.js, you can install it manually by running:
  sudo apt install -y npm
